    <section id="market">
      <h2>5. Market Analysis</h2>
      <p><strong>Industry size and trends:</strong> US residential HVAC services is a large, fragmented market (tens of billions in annual revenue) with structural tailwinds: aging installed equipment, hot Southern climate, refrigerant-regulation-driven replacement cycles, and heavy PE roll-up activity. South Carolina benefits from population in-migration and new residential construction.</p>
      <p><strong>Drivers and barriers:</strong> Drivers — replacement/upgrade demand, efficiency incentives, Sun Belt housing growth. Barriers — skilled-technician labor shortages, summer-weighted seasonality, and intense local competition including PE-backed consolidators.</p>
      <p><strong>Competitive landscape:</strong> PE-backed regional HVAC platforms (acquire at 5–8x+ EBITDA for scaled assets); independent local HVAC competitors of similar size (~2.5–3.5x SDE for owner-operator shops); national franchised brands competing on brand and lead-gen.</p>
    </section>

